FBIS4-6871 "dreas079__a94013" FBIS-EAS-94-079-A Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 ANNEX Japan Official Links Emergency Law to Constitution Official Links Emergency Law to Constitution OW2304112294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 22 Apr 94 Morning Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW2304112294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] Regarding laws to deal with emergency situations, a top Foreign Ministry official said on 21 April: "It is better to be prepared to enact such a law, but, of course, it should be within the framework of the Constitution." He thus stressed the need to be prepared to enact legislation within the framework of the current Constitution in order to respond to emergencies.
